          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " NE213 scintillation detector with diameter",
                "12.7 cm and height of 5.08 cm coupled to 12.7 cm",
                "diameter photomultiplier RCA 4522 was used for neutron",
                "detection"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Fission Fragments were counted in the fast",
                "ionization chamber. The chamber was filled with an",
                "Ar+10%C02 mixture up to 1.2 bar."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "PSD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " DYnamic THreshold method (DYTH method):",
                "Time of flight was used to determine neutron energy,",
                "pulse shape discrimination was used to distinguish",
                "between detected neutrons and gamma rays. More than",
                "70 short run measurements with total measurement time",
                "of 4500 hr were made within 4 years."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Comment by Nikolay Kornilov (2015-07-31): Spectra for",
                "each \"short runs\" were normalized in traditional way",
                "for fragments count rate, solid angle, and measured",
                "time. For verification of this procedure, ratios of",
                "experimental data to Cf-standard were calculated. The",
                "average value <R> and its standard deviation delta(R)",
                "for 2-8 MeV energy range for each \"long run\" are:",
                "1.019+-0.02 (run3), 0.993+-0.016 (run 5), 0.974+-0.023",
                " (run7). These parameters were used for an additional",
                "normalization. The experimental data, after this",
                "normalization, are compiled."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The error bars were found as a standard",
                "deviation of data for each Run. From the discussion and",
                "the AIACHNE (AI/ML Informed cAlifornium CHi Nuclear",
                "data Experiment) analysis of the late Nikolay Kornilov",
                "data, the uncertainties are statistical per his Ohio",
                "University collaborator Dr. Thomas N. Massey analysis.",
                "However, the estimated uncertainties of experimental",
                "results are less than the error bars accepted for the",
                "Cf standard. There are two possibilities:",
                "1. The experimental data are correct (systematical",
                "errors less than uncertainties of standard spectrum)",
                "and the Cf standards should be re-evaluated taking into",
                " account recommendation of this paper (for example the",
                "linear deviation from the standard spectrum).",
                "2. The deviation from the standard spectrum is due to",
                "the systematical error of the DYTH method. In this case",
                " one may estimate the uncertainties of the method.",
                "Estimated uncertainties for the DYTH method:",
                "E1-E2, MeV dS/S, %",
                "< 3        3.0",
                "3-7        2.0",
                "7-10       2.5",
                "10-13      4.0"
              ]
            }
          ],
